was about learning
the value of patience.

14:54.928 --> 14:57.929
Oh, you didn't need
to give us a bean plant
to teach us patience.

14:57.931 --> 14:59.964
You could have just said,
"ooh, you in jail."

15:01.400 --> 15:05.069
Charlie's saying
how good things come
to those who wait.

15:06.305 --> 15:07.972
Like this guy
I wanna shank.

15:07.974 --> 15:11.376
However, delaying it
till he's outta solitary

15:11.378 --> 15:14.112
Will make it all
the more gratifying,

15:14.114 --> 15:16.247
Shankwise.

15:16.249 --> 15:18.349
Really close, donovan,
really close.

15:18.351 --> 15:21.119
But I think you're confusing
delayed gratification

15:21.121 --> 15:22.654
With lying in wait.

15:22.656 --> 15:25.924
Besides,
you're not killing anybody.
We're sticking to the plan.

15:25.926 --> 15:28.927
We serve our time,
we get out, and we open
our antique shop...

15:28.929 --> 15:32.063
Both:
...In akron.

15:32.065 --> 15:34.065
What-- what cleo just said

15:34.067 --> 15:36.634
Is a great example
of delayed gratification.

15:36.636 --> 15:38.536
I can't delay
my gratification.

15:38.538 --> 15:40.638
Our showers
aren't that long.

15:40.640 --> 15:44.175
I'm talking about
relationships.

15:44.177 --> 15:46.311
As a matter of fact,
